# Module 4 Assignment: Netflix Data Visualization

## Overview
This project analyzes a Netflix dataset to generate insights into content distribution, specifically focusing on genres and ratings. The analysis is conducted using both Python and R to demonstrate data cleaning, exploration, and visualization techniques.

The project fulfills all assignment requirements, including data cleaning, statistical exploration, and creation of visualizations.

## Dataset
- File: `Netflix_shows_movies.csv`
- Description: The dataset contains information about Netflix shows and movies, including:
  - Title
  - Type (Movie/TV Show)
  - Director
  - Cast
  - Country
  - Date Added
  - Release Year
  - Rating
  - Duration
  - Genre (`listed_in`)
  - Description

## Objectives
- Clean and preprocess the dataset
- Perform exploratory data analysis
- Visualize:
  - Most watched genres
  - Ratings distribution
- Integrate R visualization

## Tools & Technologies
- Python (Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn)
- R (tidyverse, ggplot2)

